Right. We look at a city skyline, you know, at the flat tops of thousands of buildings just stretching out to the horizon, and our brains, they categorize them as passive objects.

01:06.520 --> 01:12.180
Yeah, we just assume they're resting there. Completely neutral, just, you know, shielding us from the rain.

