10:32.440 --> 10:34.800
But the paper is drawing a line in the sand.

10:35.360 --> 10:39.180
That era of cheap cheating is mathematically exhausted.

10:39.760 --> 10:41.600
The living roof is not an upgrade.

10:42.160 --> 10:45.440
No. The inert roof is a mathematical failure.

10:45.820 --> 10:52.240
And the living roof is the absolute minimum requirement for a building to exist without destroying its host city.

10:52.240 --> 10:53.620
Without destroying the city.

10:53.760 --> 10:54.020
Okay.

10:54.280 --> 11:03.140
To truly comprehend the scale of this failure, I think we have to look closely at how this rank deficiency manifests in the physical world.

11:03.400 --> 11:06.800
Let's do it. Let's look at how that computer processor overheats.

11:07.200 --> 11:10.960
Right. Let's examine the first variable in that state vector.

11:11.740 --> 11:12.900
Phi sub t.

11:13.980 --> 11:14.960
The thermal capacity.

11:15.700 --> 11:19.280
Or what the paper classifies as the thermodynamic failure.

11:19.280 --> 11:21.460
