According to the logarithmic wind law,

20:09.700 --> 20:15.320
this elevated friction physically breaks up the laminar flow into turbulent eddies.

20:15.740 --> 20:17.160
It creates turbulence.

20:17.400 --> 20:17.660
Right.

20:17.660 --> 20:21.920
And this turbulence mechanically forces the mixing of the air layers,

20:22.460 --> 20:24.980
physically shattering the thermal stratification.

20:25.500 --> 20:28.260
It actively stirs the boundary layer,

20:28.720 --> 20:33.620
breaking the heat dome apart without consuming a single watt of electrical grid power.

